WHY we are using
container_label_com_docker_compose_service

instead of
name

🔴 What OLD dashboards expect
Old Grafana dashboards (like 193, 893) were built assuming:
name="nginx"
👉 Simple container name

🟢 What NEW cAdvisor actually gives
Modern cAdvisor + Docker Compose exposes labels like:

container_label_com_docker_compose_service="grafana"
container_label_com_docker_compose_container_number="1"
container_label_com_docker_compose_project="monitoring"

👉 These come from Docker labels, not from cAdvisor itself
🔥 Why name is gone

👉 Docker changed how metadata is exposed
👉 cAdvisor now forwards Docker labels instead of custom fields
| Old                 | New            |
| ------------------- | -------------- |
| `name`              | ❌ removed      |
| `container_name`    | ❌ removed      |
| `container_label_*` | ✅ standard now |
